<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1792,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This species is widespread around the tropics, and includes a further seven synonyms (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[1248,1423,1792,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="19" refString="Mound, L. A. (2010) Thysanoptera (Thrips) of the World - a checklist. http: // www. ento. csiro. au / thysanoptera / worldthrips. html [accessed 11. iii. 2010]" type="journal article" year="2010">
Mound, 
<number box="[1356,1423,1792,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), including 
<taxonomicName box="[268,421,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilicornis">
<emphasis box="[268,421,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. exilicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[714,806,1829,1855]" name="Nigeria" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. Character states for distinguishing 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1329,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florum">
<emphasis box="[1223,1329,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. florum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the closely similar and even more widespread 
<taxonomicName box="[664,835,1867,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">
<emphasis box="[664,835,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. hawaiiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti" box="[1041,1205,1866,1892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="18" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (1999) New characters for identification of the pest species Thrips hawaiiensis and florum (Terebrantia: Thripidae). Thrips, 1, 31 - 53." type="journal article" year="1999">
Bhatti (
<number box="[1131,1196,1866,1892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. An analysis of the patterns of variation within and between populations variously identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1181,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florum">
<emphasis box="[1071,1181,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. florum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1355,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilicornis">
<emphasis box="[1197,1355,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. exilicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. hawaiiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[432,725,1941,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="19" refString="Palmer, J. M. &amp; Wetton, M. N. (1987) A morphometric analysis of the Thrips hawaiiensis (Morgan) species-group (Thysanoptera: Thripidae). Bulletin of Entomological Research, 77, 397 - 406." type="journal article" year="1987">
Palmer &amp; Wetton (
<number box="[653,717,1941,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
